{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17619639","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17619639"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T15:34:01+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T15:34:01+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16570"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16570","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16570"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.38,0.29,0.14,0.1,0.1]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9261"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75566"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9261","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9261"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16570"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61083"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"6"},{"type":"tags","id":"7"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1074"},{"type":"tags","id":"3077"},{"type":"tags","id":"3234"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5059"},{"type":"tags","id":"9014"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21941"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21944"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75566","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/75566"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 68-year-old woman with advanced Parkinson\u0027s disease experiences unpredictable \u0027off\u0027 periods despite optimised oral medication. During these \u0027off\u0027 periods, she becomes severely bradykinetic and has difficulty moving. She requires a rescue medication that can provide rapid symptom relief.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is most appropriate as a rapid rescue medication for her \u0027off\u0027 periods?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Oral levodopa/carbidopa","Sublingual pramipexole","Subcutaneous apomorphine","Intravenous apomorphine","Intranasal rotigotine"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESubcutaneous apomorphine\u003C/strong\u003E is the most appropriate rescue medication for sudden \u0027off\u0027 periods in Parkinson\u0027s disease. It is a dopamine agonist. It acts within 10 minutes of administration to manage motor symptoms until oral medications take effect.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOral levodopa/carbidopa\u003C/strong\u003E takes too long to absorb and act during an acute \u0027off\u0027 period\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPramipexole\u003C/strong\u003E is not available as a \u003Cstrong\u003Esublingual \u003C/strong\u003Eformulation, and the tablet would not provide rapid enough onset\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIntravenous apomorphine\u003C/strong\u003E is not a practical community strategy \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIntranasal rotigotine\u003C/strong\u003E does not exist - rotigotine is only available as a transdermal patch\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EApomorphine can be administered via pen injector similar to insulin devices, making it convenient for patient self-administration when needed. Common side effects include nausea, orthostatic hypotension, and injection site reactions.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Subcutaneous apomorphine injection provides rapid relief of \u0027off\u0027 periods in Parkinson\u0027s disease within 10 minutes.","Apomorphine is a potent dopamine agonist that can be used as both rescue therapy and continuous infusion.","Rescue medications are needed when oral medications fail to provide reliable symptom control in advanced Parkinson\u0027s disease."],"references":["Carbone F, Djamshidian A, Seppi K, Poewe W. Apomorphine for Parkinson\u0027s Disease: Efficacy and Safety of Current and New Formulations. CNS Drugs. 2019 Sep;33(9):905-918. doi: 10.1007/s40263-019-00661-z. PMID: 31473980; PMCID: PMC6776563.","Kobylecki C. Update on the diagnosis and management of Parkinson\u0027s disease. Clin Med (Lond). 2020 Jul;20(4):393-398. doi: 10.7861/clinmed.2020-0220. PMID: 32675145; PMCID: PMC7385761.","Armstrong MJ, Okun MS. Diagnosis and Treatment of Parkinson Disease: A Review. JAMA. 2020 Feb 11;323(6):548-560. doi: 10.1001/jama.2019.22360. PMID: 32044947."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61083"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16570"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61083","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/61083"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-30T11:21:17+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-30T11:21:42+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9261"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75566"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"6","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/6"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc75","name":"Geriatrics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"7","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/7"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udde0","name":"Neurology","synonyms":[],"description":n